description: Zurich Insurance acquires a 70% stake in Kotak Mahindra General Insurance for $670 million, marking the largest foreign investment in India's general insurance sector. The strategic move positions Zurich Insurance to tap into India's expanding insurance market, bolstering sector development and enhancing customer resilience against risks.

description: A habeas corpus petition in Andhra Pradesh High Court seeks to produce 195 bovines, including oxen and calves, unlawfully detained by police. description: Over 100 individuals in Chopda taluka, Jalgaon district fell ill after consuming panipuris at Kamalgaon weekly market. Symptoms included vomiting and loose motions, leading to hospital admissions. FDA collected samples for analysis, and authorities identified the vendor. description: A businessman in his 40s in Bengaluru was booked under the Juvenile Justice Act for letting his minor son perform dangerous stunts near Marathahalli bridge. description: Unicef's 'Child Nutrition Report 2024' reveals 181 million children under 5 in severe food poverty globally. India, China, Afghanistan, Bangladesh, and Pakistan account for 65%. Severe food poverty affects 1 in 4 children worldwide, with India at 40%. Poor diets, inadequate feeding practices, and household poverty drive this crisis, impacting both poor and non-poor households.

description: Balasore town's curfew was relaxed for four hours on Thursday, allowing essential purchases. Internet services were partially restored on leased lines from 10 am, with mobile data remaining suspended. Authorities are verifying CCTV footage to take further action on recent violence incidents. description: New research in Pediatrics highlights the importance of adequate sleep and early bedtimes for managing high blood pressure in children. Counseling on optimal sleep health is recommended for children with elevated blood pressure, supported by scientific evidence. Shortened sleep duration can have adverse effects on children, underlining the significance of sufficient sleep for overall health.

description: Mohammad Farid, also known as Aurangzeb, was brutally lynched by a mob in Aligarh, sparking outrage and protests. description: India's team management is considering the use of Kuldeep Yadav, a left-arm wrist spinner who has not played a game yet. Yadav has been seen turning his arm over for long periods in practice at Kensington Oval. Despite his impressive performance, the nature of the practice pitch and centre-wicket for the upcoming game remains uncertain, but if it is close, Kuldeep should be in the fray.
title: How can India bring Kuldeep Yadav into the playing XI?

description: In 1999, Nvidia made its debut on the Nasdaq stock exchange, eventually replacing Enron in the S&P 500. Since then, Nvidia has become the best performing stock of the last quarter-century with a total return of 591,078%. It took less than three years for Nvidia Corp. to ascend into the S&P 500 — replacing the disgraced oil-trading conglomerate Enron, no less.
title: Nvidia’s 591,078% rally to most valuable stock came in waves
Mamata Banerjee calls on BJP MP at his home, sparks speculation

description: Four minor sisters tragically drowned in UP's Balrampur while bathing in Kunaon river during a visit to their maternal grandmother's home on Bakrid.
title: 4 sisters aged 7-13 drown in UP river
If Priyanka Gandhi wins, Wayanad could become Cong's 'south bastion'

description: The founder of Oakley, the renowned eyewear company, recently made headlines by selling his Malibu property for an astonishing sum of $210 million. This staggering price tag is likely to make even the most seasoned real estate enthusiasts do a double-take. The main residence features eight bedrooms and an impressive 14 bathrooms, complemented by a well-equipped gym, and two separate guesthouses.
title: 'California's priciest home': Malibu mansion sold for...

description: A sudden shower on Monday night and Tuesday morning reduced humidity, but the Indian contingent would hope it was a one-off event. Rohit Sharma hoped the game against Afghanistan in Super-8s would not be curtailed, as India are ahead in a 20-over contest on a good pitch. The Indian contingent hopes the rain is a one-off.
title: Super 8s: Cues for India from Windies win against Afghanistan

description: Rauf and five other players including Pakistan captain Babar Azam, Mohammad Amir, Imad Wasim, Shadab Khan, and Azam Khan have decided to spend their holidays in London before returning to Pakistan after their disastrous T20 World Cup campaign. The above-mentioned players plan to spend time with friends and family in London.
title: 'Pak or India...': Rizwan on Rauf's scuffle with fan

description: A man was killed and others injured in a targeted shooting at a food outlet in Rajouri Garden. Over a dozen rounds were fired at the Burger King outlet, causing panic in the area.
title: One dead as armed men open fire at Burger King outlet in Delhi
Over 550 Hajj pilgrims die in Mecca amid extreme heat

description: A 21-year-old man, Surya, was fatally run over by Beeda Madhuri, daughter of YSR Congress Rajya Sabha MP Beeda Masthan Rao, while sleeping on the pavement at Besant Nagar near Tiger Varadachari Salai. Vanitha, his wife, found him asleep on the road after an argument and got drunk the previous night.
title: YSR Congress MP’s daughter runs over man sleeping on sidewalk

description: Kane Williamson has resigned as captain of New Zealand's white-ball teams and will not sign a national contract for the 2024/25 season, following the Black Caps' early exit from the T20 World Cup. New Zealand has reached semi-finals in the last three T20 World Cups but has not won an ICC white-ball title.
title: Kane Williamson steps down as NZ captain, declines contract

description: IMD forecasts heatwave in North India until Wednesday due to an approaching western disturbance towards northwest India. Punjab, Haryana, Delhi, Uttar Pradesh, Himachal Pradesh, Uttarakhand, Bihar, and Madhya Pradesh experience heatwave conditions. Maximum temperatures in the region reach 47.6 degrees Celsius in Prayagraj.
title: Heatwave to continue over many parts of North India: IMD
Bangal train crash: 'Why blame dead man even before probe'

description: After a promising start in June, the long-awaited monsoon in Haveri district has taken a shocking break, leading to dry weather and a unique practice of exhuming bodies with skin diseases to revive rain.
title: This Karnataka district exhumes bodies to appease rain god

description: In a midnight operation, police retrieved Darshan's loafers from his wife Vijayalakshmi's flat in south Bengaluru in connection to the Renukaswamy murder case. Darshan's employee Babul Khan and aide Pavan K assisted in the search. The loafers were traced to Mysuru through Darshan's costume assistant Raju. FSL officials seized the loafers, and Police commissioner B Dayananda pledged justice for the victim's family.
title: Loafers Darshan kicked his fan with found in wife’s flat

description: Apple reaches settlement with EU to avoid fine in antitrust probe on Apple Pay. The company to make concessions for rivals' access to contactless tech system.
title: How Apple may settle contactless payments inquiry with the EU

description: The ancient Jagannath temple in Kanpur is renowned for its accurate prediction of the monsoon arrival. A team from the meteorological department of Chandra Shekhar Azad University of Agriculture and Technology predicted heavy rain this season based on the temple's mystical tradition. The temple's stone slab starts dripping days before the monsoon, and this year, significant drops indicate a good rainfall forecast.
title: Kanpur’s ‘monsoon temple’ has spoken: Good rainfall this year

description: Congress party's decision to have Rahul Gandhi retain the Rae Bareli seat, a legacy of his family, has been well received by the cadre and locals in the high-profile parliamentary constituency. The move has energized the party's state brass, with long-standing supporters expressing delight over the decision.
title: Rae Bareli janta celebrates as Rahul Gandhi retains family seat

description: The world's number one batter Suryakumar Yadav has had to change his game due to the nature of the wickets in the T20 World Cup but he is expecting the surfaces in the Caribbean to be a lot better for strokeplay. India open their Super 8 campaign against Afghanistan here on Thursday. Their other games are against Bangladesh and Australia in St Lucia, which has produced the tournament's highest total thus far, and Antigua.
title: 'If you are No. 1, you should...': Suryakumar Yadav

description: NORTHKOREA-Putin and Kim embrace in North Korea, vow new multi-polar world
title: Putin meets Kim in first visit to Pyongyang in two decades
